cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on the properties of deep neural networks and their expressivity. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of DNNs for image classification, which suggests it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The study of decision boundaries and optimization techniques also suggests it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the relevance of surrounding regions, which could suggest it belongs to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and understanding the context of words.
